a) Functional and Non-Functional Requirements of E-Ticketing System

Functional Requirements (What the system should do)

1. User Registration & Login

Users should be able to create accounts and log in securely.



2. Search for Tickets

Users can search for buses/trains/flights based on date, time, source, destination.



3. View Available Seats

System shows seat availability in real-time.



4. Ticket Booking

Users can select seats and book tickets.



5. Payment Processing

System supports online payment (UPI, card, wallet, net banking).



6. Generate E-Ticket

System generates a digital ticket (PDF/Email/SMS).



7. Cancel Ticket

Users can cancel booked tickets and receive refunds.



8. Booking History

Users can view previous & active bookings.



9. Admin Management

Admin can add/edit/delete schedules, routes, prices.



10. Notifications



Email/SMS notifications on booking, cancellation, delays.



---

Non-Functional Requirements (Quality of the system)

1. Performance

System must load results within 3–5 seconds.



2. Scalability

Should support large numbers of concurrent users.



3. Security

Encrypted passwords, secure payments, data protection.

Must follow SSL/HTTPS.



4. Availability

System should be available 24×7.



5. Reliability

Should not lose data during transactions.



6. Usability

Easy-to-use UI for all age groups.



7. Maintainability

Easy updates without downtime.



8. Compatibility

Work on mobile, tablets, laptops, all browsers.





---

